radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is slightly dilated and measures up to 9 mm in diameter with adjacent fat stranding and probably reactive wall thickening of the adjacent terminal ileum. No focal fluid collection or free fluid. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. Abdomen shows no evidence of focal lesions, biliary dilatation, hydronephrosis, nephrolithiasis, or retroperitoneal/mesenteric lymphadenopathy.
